 title=3D"Ellipsoidal coordinates">Ellipsoidal coordinates</a></div>
<p>It is also possible to deal with ellipsoids in Cartesian coordinates by =
using a modified version of the spherical coordinates.=20
</p><p>Let P be an ellipsoid specified by the level set
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle ax^{2}+by^{2}+cz^{2}=3Dd.}">
