        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle ax^{2}+by^{2}=
+cz^{2}=3Dd.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/827cb48eb0365b2d3fd9836f2240073b7bbd1425" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.671ex; width:20.619ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle a=
x^{2}+by^{2}+cz^{2}=3Dd.}"></span>
</p><p>The modified spherical coordinates of a point in P in the ISO conven=
tion (i.e. for physics: <i>radius</i> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D=
"font-style:italic;">r</span>, <i>inclination</i> <span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=B8</span>, <i>azimuth</i> <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=86</span>) can be obtain=
ed from its <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cartesian_coordinate_s=
ystem" title=3D"Cartesian coordinate system">Cartesian coordinates</a> <spa=
n class=3D"texhtml">(<i>x</i>, <i>y</i>, <i>z</i>)</span> by the formulae
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle {\begin{aligned}x&amp;=3D{\frac {1}{\sqrt {a}}}r\sin \t=
heta \,\cos \varphi ,\\y&amp;=3D{\frac {1}{\sqrt {b}}}r\sin \theta \,\sin \=
varphi ,\\z&amp;=3D{\frac {1}{\sqrt {c}}}r\cos \theta ,\\r^{2}&amp;=3Dax^{2=
}+by^{2}+cz^{2}.\end{aligned}}}">
